    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>

<p>Find the cofactors of \(x,y,z\) in the following determinant:</p>
\[\begin{vmatrix} {@AA[1,1]@} &amp; {@AA[1,2]@} &amp; {@AA[1,3]@} \\ {@AA[2,1]@} &amp; {@AA[2,2]@} &amp; {@AA[2,3]@} \\ x &amp; y &amp; z \end{vmatrix}\]

<p>Cofactor of \(x\): [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>
<p>Cofactor of \(y\): [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]] [[feedback:prt2]]</p>
<p>Cofactor of \(z\): [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]] [[feedback:prt3]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[To obtain the cofactor of an element of a \(3 \times 3\) matrix we multiply the minor of that element by the corresponding sign from the \(3 \times 3\) array of signs.<br>We are given the determinant: \(\begin{vmatrix} {@AA[1,1]@} &amp; {@AA[1,2]@} &amp; {@AA[1,3]@} \\ {@AA[2,1]@} &amp; {@AA[2,2]@} &amp; {@AA[2,3]@} \\ x &amp; y &amp; z \end{vmatrix}.\)<br><p>For \(x\), the sign is \(+\), and the minor is \(\det {@MMx@}\). Hence the cofactor is \({@ta1@}.\)</p><p>For \(y\), the sign is \(-\), and the minor is \(\det {@MMy@}\). Hence the cofactor is \({@ta2@}.\)</p><p>For \(z\), the sign is \(+\) again, and the minor is \(\det {@MMz@}\). Hence the cofactor is \({@ta3@}.\)</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
